Rating: 4
Easy, elegant. I heeded the advice of other reviewers and blanched the asparagus for just over a minute. I mixed herbed Boursin with 1/8 cup of Dijon. I folded whole slices of prosciutto in half, smeared with the cheese-mustard mixture, and rolled up each slice around two spears of asparagus, leaving both the steam ends and tips exposed. I chilled the asparagus until cold before I rolled it, assembled the night before, then refrigerated overnight in a plastic container with waxed paper between each layer.

