Rating: 0
I made these for a Christmas party and they quickly disappeared! I cooked the asparagus in 1 can of chicken broth mixed with 1 cup of water. I cooked for 1 ½ minutes and then moved the asparagus to a bowl of ice water. I cooked the asparagus the day before the party and stored in a zip-lock bag in the refrigerator until the afternoon of the party when I rolled them. Like previous posters, I combined the cheese and mustard together before spreading on the Prosciutto. Be careful that your Prosciutto isnt cut too thin or it will tear apart when spreading. Next time I will ask the deli person to put a piece of plastic between each slice. I had some leftover that I didnt get rolled before the party and rolled them for myself the next day. I refrigerated a few of them overnight and actually thought they were better having set rolled and refrigerated overnight, so will do that next time.

