Rating: 4
I agree with the other reviewer who said that 2 mins is too long to cook the asparagus - I cooked for 1 1/2 mins and almost wished that I had cooked them for less. I definitely just got messy with it and took the other reviewers' advice to spread on the cheese and mustard separately with my finger - having 2 clean paper towels nearby. 1 paper towel cleaned my work surface after each roll and the other one cleaned my fingers after spreading on the cheese and mustard before rolling - for a nice clean presentation. I was concerned that they were going to be too messy to eat but about 1/2 hour in the fridge after preparation firmed everything up (including the sloppy cheese) and made it all perfect. These went very fast and were eaten up but some seriously finicky and stuffy folks. Thanks for all of the other advice - truly helpful!

