Rating: 1
I agree with the previous reviewer. Wrap asparagus spears in proscuitto, then phyllo (leaving tip exposed), sprinkle with parmesan and bake until the phyllo is golden brown. You can serve them whole or cut them (on the diagonal) into bite size pieces...those seemed to go over better than this recipe, and they aren't as messy. Plus, they can be made pretty far in advance (cover with damp paper towels and saran wrap) and baked at the last minute.

Rating: 4
